&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Theatre Practitioner - Anaesthetics| Band 5/6 | Permanent |Bank| Excellent development opportunities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spire Manchester is looking for a highly motivated and experienced Theatre Practitioner to join our high performing Theatre Team, with a focus on anaesthetics this is your opportunity to join one of the UK’s best private hospitals and take your career to the next level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spire Manchester Hospital is a brand new, £65m state-of-the-art healthcare facility offering patients a wide range of integrated surgical, medical and diagnostic services. The rapidly expanding team in Manchester consists of over 500 colleagues, who thrive in the welcoming atmosphere that is friendly, supportive and progressive&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties and responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful Theatre Practitioner will assist in scrubbing for Consultant led surgeries that vary in complexity and specialism, such as orthopedics, cosmetics, gynae and ENT to name a few. You will assess patient’s health and well-being across a complex and changing caseload, and develop care plans that are appropriate to the patient, taking into consideration the care pathway, perioperative risks and their wellbeing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Qualified ODP/Scrub Nurse.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 2 years scrub experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will be highly motivated and used to working in challenging but rewarding environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer employees a competitive salary as well as a comprehensive benefits package which includes but is not limited to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;competitive hourly rate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Free onsite gym and parking&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please see the attached benefits leaflet under ‘’additional information’’ for more details.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We commit to our employees well-being through work life balance, on-going development, support and reward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spire Healthcare is a leading independent hospital group that has been putting patients at the heart of everything we do for over 40 years. We have 39 hospitals, 10 clinics and a Specialist Cancer Care Centre across England, Wales and Scotland.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information about this role or for an informal conversation about the range of career options available with Spire please contact claire.murphy@spirehealthcare.com&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;For us, &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;it&#39;s more than just treating patients; it&#39;s about looking after people. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
